men's. Building and using a one-of-a-kind database that covers 193 countries, this book systematically analyzes how far we've come and how far we have to go in adopting evidence-based solutions to close the gaps. Spanning topics including girls' education, employment discrimination of all kinds, sexual harassment, and caregiving needs across the life course, the authors bring the findings to life through global maps, stories of laws' impact in courts and beyond, and case studies of making change. A powerful call to action, Equality within Our Lifetimes reveals how gender equality is both feasible and urgently needed to address some of the greatest challenges of our generation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2023) 0aEquality before the law. 0aEqualityxEconomic aspects. 0aSex discrimination in employment. 0aSex discriminationxEconomic aspects. 7aLAW / Gender & the Law.2bisacsh1 aRaub, Amy, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSprague, Aleta, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut40uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520392304zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520392304zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520392304/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA  aZDB-23-UCY